9 D. 1. The Director of Service Oklahoma is hereby authorized to
10 adopt rules as may be necessary to enter into reciprocity agreements
11 with foreign countries. The rules shall specify that the driver
12 license standards of the foreign country shall be comparable to
13 those of this state. The rules shall also require foreign drivers,
14 who are operating a motor vehicle in Oklahoma under such a
15 reciprocity agreement, to comply with the compulsory motor vehicle
16 liability insurance and financial responsibility laws of this state.
17 2. Service Oklahoma shall enter into a reciprocity agreement
18 for driver licenses with the country of Ireland.
19 E. When an automated driving system, as defined by Section 1701
20 of this title, installed on a motor vehicle is engaged, the
21 following shall apply:
22 1. The automated driving system is considered the driver or
23 operator, for the purpose of assessing compliance with applicable
24 traffic or motor vehicle laws, and shall be deemed to satisfy
